{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}} {{Use British English|date=April 2015}} {{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Benefits Agency |type = Executive Agency |nativename = |nativename_a = |nativename_r = |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |formed = 1991 |preceding1 = [[Department of Social Security]] |dissolved = 2001 |superseding = [[Jobcentre Plus]] |jurisdiction = [[United Kingdom]] |headquarters = |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = |minister1_pfo = |parent_department = [[Department of Social Security]] }}
The '''Benefits Agency''' (BA) was an [[executive agency]] of the [[United Kingdom]] [[Department of Social Security]] (subsequently the [[Department for Work and Pensions]]) which was set up in 1991 to "help create and deliver an active modern social security service, which encourages and enables independence and aims to pay the right money at the right time".<ref>"Resource Accounts 2000-2001". Department of Social Security, 2002</ref> The BA was merged with the Employment Service in April 2001 to form [[Jobcentre Plus]].
